snippet: The elections brought an end to the eight-year dominance of President Mikheil Saakashvili and his team, and their push to introduce Western ways to this conservative society.
abstract: Georgia's elections bring end to eight-year dominance of Pres Mikheil Saakashvili and his team, and their push to introduce Western ways to this conservative society;  country’s Orthodox church repeatedly stated its neutrality in race but signaled voters that it was not endorsing the government.
lead_paragraph: The elections brought an end to the eight-year dominance of President Mikheil Saakashvili and his team, and their push to introduce Western ways to this conservative society.

headline.seo: Church’s Muscle Aided Win of President’s Rivals in Georgia
headline.main: Church’s Muscle Helped Propel President’s Rivals to Victory in Georgia
headline.print_headline: Church’s Muscle Helped Propel President’s Rivals to Victory in Georgia
